[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hey, I'm told that the red/black tree is deprecated and shouldn't be used for new code. <br>\nOne use of the red/black tree we have in binder is the range allocator, where we have a collection of objects of various sizes, and we want to look up the smallest object with size at least some lower bound. Any ideas?</p>",
        "id": 365639606,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1686592738
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>cc <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"531558\">@Wedson Almeida Filho</span></p>",
        "id": 365639858,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1686592792
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess it totally does have a method for that. Neat.</p>",
        "id": 365642434,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1686593447
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I vaguely remember there is some range API</p>",
        "id": 365642809,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1686593548
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Has anyone else worked on xarray bindings?</p>",
        "id": 365643912,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1686593829
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There is <a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20230224-rust-xarray-v3-1-04305b1173a5@asahilina.net/\">https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20230224-rust-xarray-v3-1-04305b1173a5@asahilina.net/</a> from Lina -- it is waiting for a review from Matthew Wilcox (i.e. the maintainer).</p>",
        "id": 365646565,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1686594478
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am using the radix tree for key/value store. But it is deprecated in favor of xarray as well.</p>",
        "id": 365666220,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1686598863
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Okay, I guess it would make sense to resend the patch and ping Matthew?</p>",
        "id": 365666507,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1686598959
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would suggest replying to Lina's thread putting Matthew in the <code>To:</code> and asking him directly (e.g. \"Matthew, would you ...\") and saying that you also need the abstraction. That way it is clear more people need it.</p>\n<p>Then <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"522295\">@Asahi Lina</span> may also want to do the \"RESEND\" on top of that, and mention the need from you too.</p>",
        "id": 365673218,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1686600964
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Finally tinkering with this...I would like to add some doctests and then expose more of the underlying API (like <code>xa_find_after</code>) that we likely need for binder. A couple questions:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>I know this has been mentioned recently so forgive me for re-asking...when will the <a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/rust-for-linux/20230614180837.630180-1-ojeda@kernel.org/\">kunit patch set</a> get merged into <code>rust-next</code>? After the recent <a href=\"https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/releases/tag/rust-6.5\">set of changes for the current merge window</a> is accepted?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Having cherry picked the <a href=\"http://\">xarray patch</a> onto <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"411477\">@Miguel Ojeda</span> 's <a href=\"https://github.com/ojeda/linux/tree/rust-next-kunit\">rust-next-kunit branch</a>, I'm struggling a bit with the <code>Pin</code> API that <code>XArray</code> requires:</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/// Replaces an entry with a new value, dropping the old value (if any).</span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">set</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;&amp;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">index</span>: <span class=\"kt\">usize</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">value</span>: <span class=\"nc\">T</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nb\">Result</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I am trying to follow the pin_init documentation and my head is spinning. I blame the reader :)</p>\n<p>What is the right way to do something like this? I followed the first compiler error, but I suspect I should use one of the macros in <code>init.rs</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/// An array which efficiently maps sparse integer indices to owned objects.</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// This is similar to a `Vec&lt;Option&lt;T&gt;&gt;`, but more efficient when there are holes in the</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// index space, and can be efficiently grown.</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// This structure is expected to often be used with an inner type that can either be efficiently</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// cloned, such as an `Arc&lt;T&gt;`.</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// # Examples</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// Here is a basic example just to see if it compiles :)</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// ```</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// use kernel::xarray::{XArray, flags::LOCK_IRQ};</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// use kernel::sync::Arc;</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// let value = Arc::try_new(1).unwrap();</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// let xarray: XArray&lt;Arc&lt;usize&gt;&gt; = XArray::new(LOCK_IRQ);</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// Pin::new(xarray).set(1, value).unwrap();</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// # Ok::&lt;(), Error&gt;(())</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// ```</span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">XArray</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span>: <span class=\"nc\">ForeignOwnable</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">xa</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Opaque</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span>::<span class=\"n\">xarray</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">_p</span>: <span class=\"nc\">PhantomData</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">_q</span>: <span class=\"nc\">PhantomPinned</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I'm assuming this is hard to explain asynchronously  so  I'm much obliged to meet if/when someone is willing.</p>\n<p>p.s. happy to resend the patch/ping Matthew as well.</p>",
        "id": 368738005,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Gilbride",
        "timestamp": 1687488750
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Does</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">xarray</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span>::<span class=\"n\">pin</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">XArray</span>::<span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">LOCK_IRQ</span><span class=\"p\">));</span>\n<span class=\"n\">xarray</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">set</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>works for you?</p>",
        "id": 368754552,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1687497578
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess you need pin projection to call those methods without <code>Pin</code>/<code>Box</code></p>",
        "id": 368807035,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1687509696
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>.when will the kunit patch set get merged into rust-next? After the recent set of changes for the current merge window is accepted?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>After the merge window is over, i.e. when <code>v6.5-rc1</code> gets tagged, which should happen on July 9th.</p>\n<p>Also note that it may go through the KUnit tree, rather than the Rust one. In that case, you will see them in <a href=\"https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/shuah/linux-kselftest.git/log/?h=kunit\">https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/shuah/linux-kselftest.git/log/?h=kunit</a> instead of <code>rust-next</code>.</p>",
        "id": 368826077,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1687513440
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Having said that, we can have them in <code>rust-dev</code> at any point, since that branch is not in <code>linux-next</code>.</p>",
        "id": 368828825,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1687513965
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also, you could send them sooner, i.e. independently of the KUnit getting merged(since you don't have a hard dependency on it).</p>",
        "id": 368829312,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1687514077
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>As for XArray, if you want to send them before that gets merged, then you could do so, noting in the cover letter it depends on that particular patch.</p>",
        "id": 368829882,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1687514176
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"411647\">Boqun Feng</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/Red.2Fblack.20tree.20deprecation/near/368754552\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Does</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">xarray</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span>::<span class=\"n\">pin</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">XArray</span>::<span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">LOCK_IRQ</span><span class=\"p\">));</span>\n<span class=\"n\">xarray</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">set</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>works for you?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Maybe there is something I need to do in order to use Box with the new kunit doctests? Here is the branch where I patched in the kunit set and the xarray commit above: <a href=\"https://github.com/matthewtgilbride/linux/commits/rust-next-xarray\">https://github.com/matthewtgilbride/linux/commits/rust-next-xarray</a></p>\n<p>I get various errors just trying to create <code>Box</code> instances e.g.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">ERROR</span>:<span class=\"nc\">root</span>:<span class=\"nc\">error</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">E0658</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>: <span class=\"nc\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">unstable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">library</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">feature</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">allocator_api</span><span class=\"o\">'</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"o\">-</span>-&gt; <span class=\"nc\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">doctests_kernel_generated</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>:<span class=\"mi\">2877</span>:<span class=\"mi\">14</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">2877</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">my_box</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span>::<span class=\"n\">try_new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"mi\">2878</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">my_box</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span>::<span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">                   </span><span class=\"o\">^^^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">function</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">or</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">associated</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">item</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">found</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 368888116,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Gilbride",
        "timestamp": 1687525438
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>you need to use <code>try_new</code> because the kernel uses fallible allocations, there is no <code>new</code> available</p>",
        "id": 368903530,
        "sender_full_name": "Ariel Miculas",
        "timestamp": 1687528123
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In the test, I have this on the first line when attempting to use <code>try_new</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/// #![feature(allocator_api)]</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>But I still get that \"use of unstable library feature\" error.  I'm assuming this has something to do with the kunit absraction.  <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"411477\">@Miguel Ojeda</span> ?</p>",
        "id": 368905070,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Gilbride",
        "timestamp": 1687528423
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>try adding <code>allocator_api</code> to <code>rust_allowed_features</code> in <code>scripts/Makefile.build</code></p>",
        "id": 368906685,
        "sender_full_name": "Ariel Miculas",
        "timestamp": 1687528729
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">rust_allowed_features</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>:<span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">allocator_api</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"n\">new_uninit</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 368906868,
        "sender_full_name": "Ariel Miculas",
        "timestamp": 1687528764
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That did it, thanks! This unblocks me locally at the moment...<em>should</em> this feature be enabled though?</p>",
        "id": 368910396,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Gilbride",
        "timestamp": 1687529421
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>enabling this feature is fine, we use it in the kernel already</p>",
        "id": 368910521,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1687529448
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>AFAIK the <code>rust_allowed_features</code> variable determines the features that are enabled/allowed for crates that are not the <code>kernel</code> crate (e.g. modules and doc tests as they are run in a separate crate IIRC)</p>",
        "id": 368911037,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1687529537
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"546447\">y86</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/Red.2Fblack.20tree.20deprecation/near/368910521\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>enabling this feature is fine, we use it in the kernel already</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Should I go ahead and send a tiny patch for this?</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"411647\">Boqun Feng</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/Red.2Fblack.20tree.20deprecation/near/368754552\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Does</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">xarray</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span>::<span class=\"n\">pin</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">XArray</span>::<span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">LOCK_IRQ</span><span class=\"p\">));</span>\n<span class=\"n\">xarray</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">set</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>works for you?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I similarly don't have access to <code>Box::pin</code> in this scenario.  I tried this, but end up with <code>Pin&lt;Box&lt;XArray&lt;_&gt;&gt;&gt;</code> instead of <code>Pin&lt;XArray&lt;_&gt;&gt;</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">my_xarray</span>: <span class=\"nc\">XArray</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">XArray</span>::<span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">LOCK_IRQ</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">my_xarray</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">XArray</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span>::<span class=\"n\">into_pin</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span>::<span class=\"n\">try_new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">my_xarray</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">());</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">// not a Pin&lt;XArray&lt;_&gt;&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"n\">my_xarray</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">set</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 368915844,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Gilbride",
        "timestamp": 1687530468
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"582232\">Matt Gilbride</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/Red.2Fblack.20tree.20deprecation/near/368915844\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"546447\">y86</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/Red.2Fblack.20tree.20deprecation/near/368910521\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>enabling this feature is fine, we use it in the kernel already</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Should I go ahead and send a tiny patch for this?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Just enable it in the patch where you need it.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"411647\">Boqun Feng</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/288089-General/topic/Red.2Fblack.20tree.20deprecation/near/368754552\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Does</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">xarray</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span>::<span class=\"n\">pin</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">XArray</span>::<span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">LOCK_IRQ</span><span class=\"p\">));</span>\n<span class=\"n\">xarray</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">set</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>works for you?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I similarly don't have access to <code>Box::pin</code> in this scenario.  I tried this, but end up with <code>Pin&lt;Box&lt;XArray&lt;_&gt;&gt;&gt;</code> instead of <code>Pin&lt;XArray&lt;_&gt;&gt;</code>:</p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">my_xarray</span>: <span class=\"nc\">XArray</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">XArray</span>::<span class=\"n\">new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">LOCK_IRQ</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">my_xarray</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Pin</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">XArray</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span>::<span class=\"n\">into_pin</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nb\">Box</span>::<span class=\"n\">try_new</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">my_xarray</span><span class=\"p\">).</span><span class=\"n\">unwrap</span><span class=\"p\">());</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">// not a Pin&lt;XArray&lt;_&gt;&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"n\">my_xarray</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">set</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This makes sense, since <code>Pin</code> is a wrapper for pointers and <code>XArray</code> is not a pointer. To get <code>Pin&lt;&amp;XArray&lt;_&gt;&gt;</code> you should use <code>Pin::as_ref()</code></p>",
        "id": 368918697,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1687531002
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>At last...being verbose for my own understanding...thanks for the help!</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/// # Examples</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// Flailing about at an example : - P</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// ```</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// use kernel::xarray::{XArray, flags::LOCK_IRQ};</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// let my_xarray: XArray&lt;Box&lt;u32&gt;&gt; = XArray::new(LOCK_IRQ);</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// let my_xarray: Pin&lt;Box&lt;XArray&lt;Box&lt;u32&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; = Box::into_pin(Box::try_new(my_xarray).unwrap());</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// let my_xarray: Pin&lt;&amp;XArray&lt;Box&lt;u32&gt;&gt;&gt; = my_xarray.as_ref();</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// // yay!</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// my_xarray.set(1, Box::try_new(1).unwrap());</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// assert!(my_xarray.get(1).is_some());</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// assert!(my_xarray.get(2).is_none());</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">///</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// # Ok::&lt;(), Error&gt;(())</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// ```</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 368924717,
        "sender_full_name": "Matt Gilbride",
        "timestamp": 1687532019
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can also use <code>?</code> instead of <code>unwrap</code> in documentation examples (which is usually what one wants in the kernel).</p>",
        "id": 368928069,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1687532609
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah right, I was missing the <code>as_ref</code>, thank <span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"546447\">y86</span> ;-)</p>",
